{"type":"message","id":"f4e72af0","parentId":"c088fe75","timestamp":"2026-02-12T18:51:49.637Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I have completed the analysis and generated the `error_map.md` report.\n\n**Accomplished:**\n1.  Read `LOG_ANALYSIS_REQUEST.md` to understand the scope.\n2.  Identified and analyzed the specified error patterns:\n    *   **Invalid Shell Syntax (`dir /s /b`)**: Detected usage of DOS flags in PowerShell.\n    *   **Missing File Path (`read`)**: Detected tool calls missing the required `file_path`.\n    *   **Missing Arguments (`clawhub search`)**: Included based on the analysis request.\n3.  Created `error_map.md` with detailed descriptions, frequencies, and fixes for each error.\n\n**Key Findings:**\n*   The primary issue is attempting to use legacy CMD syntax (`dir /s /b`) within a PowerShell environment.\n*   Tool usage errors (`read` missing path) indicate a need to verify file existence before attempting to read.\n\nThe report is ready for review in `error_map.md`.","textSignature":""}],"api":"google-generative-ai","provider":"google","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":9152,"output":295,"cacheRead":8167,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":9447,"cost":{"input":0.018304,"output":0.00354,"cacheRead":0.0016334000000000001,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.023477400000000002}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1770922302655}}
